" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/21 6:34am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Custome UI's:  How to, Examples, and Resources.  - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Edited:</span>&nbsp;11/21 7:18am (1 edits total) <span style="font-weight: bold;">Edited By:</span> <a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Phryer_Tuck?boards=vn " style="color: Orange;font-weight: bold;font-style: normal;background-color: DarkBlue;text-decoration: none;border-top: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-bottom: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-right: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-left: 1px solid DarkBlue;">Phryer_Tuck</a></td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight:bold;">What is the Magic Interface number?</span> <br> Start WOW and look in the lower left for a number in brackets like this (4062). That's the magic number. This number tells the UI what&#8217;s new and updates the UI for the new patch.  <br>  <br> Once you have this number open your World of Warcraft/Interface/AddOns folder and look for any and all files with a .toc extension. Inside each one of those files you&#8217;ll see a line &quot;## Interface: 4062&quot; just change the number to reflect the new patch and re-enter WOW. <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;">At anytime you can reload the interface by typing the following command:</span> <br> /console reloadui <br>  <br> I have found sometimes this does not totally refresh the UI. <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Make Shift &#8226; OverSoul &#8226; Atticus &#8226; McBane &#8226; Threepio &#8226; Wyatt Herb  &#8226; Apoch &#8226; Tom Sawyer <br> Just because your paranoid doesn't not mean I'm not after you <br> Follow the Cult | <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cultofxen.com">http://www.cultofxen.com</a> <br> Ner'zhul PvP - Pacific Server <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="