ght: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-left: 1px solid DarkBlue;">Phryer_Tuck</a></td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight:bold;">From the Creators of Cosmos &amp; CT Mod: &quot;Sea&quot; or better known as wowwiki.com</span> <br>  <br> A little while ago, Cide and I got together to discuss the future of WoW UI Modding. We realized that there's a lot of commonality between UI mods, and that many coders are redoing the same type of work.  <br>  <br> We also realized that a lot of new modders could use a solid feature library to speed up their developement. So we began work on &quot;Sea&quot;:  <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.wowwiki.com/index.php/Sea">http://www.wowwiki.com/index.php/Sea</a> <br>  <br> Sea is a function library designed to work like java. for example:  <br>  Sea.io.print(&quot;Hello World!&quot;);  <br>  <br>  <br> This kind of library makes developing mods easier, faster and more consistent. We're still in the first stages of designing this Library, but we look forward to a lot of future development. Cosmos itself is using Sea and soon so will its AddOns.  <br>  <br> If you want to check out the early version of Sea, it is available at:  <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cosmosui.org/test/Sea.zip">http://www.cosmosui.org/test/Sea.zip</a> <br>  <br> Clear documentation is available at the WoW Wiki website (http://www.wowwiki.com) and if you have suggestions, please login and leave them on the Discussion tabs of the Sea pages!  <br>  <br> Thanks for reading!  <br> -Alexander Yoshi <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Make Shift &#8226; OverSoul &#8226; Atticus &#8226; McBane &#8226; Threepio &#8226; Wyatt Herb  &#8226; Apoch &#8226; Tom Sawyer <br> Just because your paranoid doesn't not mean I'm not after you <br> Follow the Cult | <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cultofxen.com">http://www.cultofxen.com</a> <br> Ner'zhul PvP - Pacific Server <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=22852&topic=79108902">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=79112095" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=195775">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=195775">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Phryer_Tuck?boards=vn " style="color: Orange;font-weight: bold;font-style: normal;background-color: DarkBlue;text-decoration: none;border-top: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-bottom: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-right: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-left: 1px solid DarkBlue;">Phryer_Tuck</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=http://media.ign.com/boardimages/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="3,280 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Phryer_Tuck"><font size="1">collection (7)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Phryer_Tuck"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Title:</span> <b>WoW Vault Staff</b> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 3,280<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Jun 01<br></span><img border=0 hspace=8 vspace=8 src="http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/dexter2.gif" width="80" height="80" alt="5264" name="5264" id="5264" class="IconImage"><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/21 7:33am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Custome UI's:  How to, Examples, and Resources. </td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight:bold;">How do I install a UI mod?</span>  <br> Its really simple all you need to do is extract any downloaded files into your World of Warcraft Interface folder. If that folder does not exist just create a folder and call it &#8220;Interface&#8221;. What happens is WOW registers all UI mods at login, and the way it does this is by reading any set of files in the AddOns folder. So all a savvy programmer need do, is create a set of UI mod files, and place them in the AddOns folder.  <br>  <br> In a standard installition your WOW folder structure should look like the below picture. If it does not cut and paste the files so your folder structure matches the below: <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink target=_blank href="http://www.cultofxen.com/images/ui/folder_structure.jpg"><img border=1 width=160 height=120 hspace=5 vspace=5 src="http://www.cultofxen.com/images/ui/folder_structure.jpg"></a> <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Make Shift &#8226; OverSoul &#8226; Atticus &#8226; McBane &#8226; Threepio &#8226; Wyatt Herb  &#8226; Apoch &#8226; Tom Sawyer <br> Just because your paranoid doesn't not mean I'm not after you <br> Follow the Cult | <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cultofxen.com">http://www.cultofxen.com</a> <br> Ner'zhul PvP - Pacific Server <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=22852&topic=79108902">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=79112345" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=195775">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=195775">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Phryer_Tuck?boards=vn " style="color: Orange;font-weight: bold;font-style: normal;background-color: DarkBlue;text-decoration: none;border-top: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-bottom: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-right: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-left: 1px solid DarkBlue;">Phryer_Tuck</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=http://media.ign.com/boardimages/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="3,280 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Phryer_Tuck"><font size="1">collection (7)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Phryer_Tuck"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Title:</span> <b>WoW Vault Staff</b> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 3,280<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Jun 01<br></span><img border=0 hspace=8 vspace=8 src="http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/dexter2.gif" width="80" height="80" alt="5264" name="5264" id="5264" class="IconImage"><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/21 7:48am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Custome UI's:  How to, Examples, and Resources.  - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Edited:</span>&nbsp;11/22 12:17pm (1 edits total) <span style="font-weight: bold;">Edited By:</span> <a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Phryer_Tuck?boards=vn " style="color: Orange;font-weight: bold;font-style: normal;background-color: DarkBlue;text-decoration: none;border-top: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-bottom: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-right: 1px solid DarkBlue;border-left: 1px solid DarkBlue;">Phryer_Tuck</a></td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight:bold;">What is the WOW API?</span> <br> An API is an abbreviation for &quot;Application Programming Interface,&quot; by which an application program (a complete program that performs a specific function directly for the user) can access the computer's operating system. What this means is there is a lot of commands you have access to that can make your macro or mob do more then just emote /v silly. You can find the WOW API here: <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cosmosui.org/texts/BlizzardCommands.xml">http://www.cosmosui.org/texts/BlizzardCommands.xml</a> - This is an old list, please refer to <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.wowwiki.com">http://www.wowwiki.com</a> for a more up todate listing of API commands. <br>  <br> And here is a good example of how to use a few of those functions inside a macro. <br>  <br> <blockquote>/script TargetUnit(&quot;player&quot;);   <br> /script UseContainerItem(4,4);  <br>  <br> On the UseContainerItem, the (4,4) specifies that I want to find an item in the last bag at slot 4. Figure out where you want to put your bandages and use the grid slot in the macro.  <br>  <br> The bag numbers are 0 - 4 (0 being the big 16-slot bag you get by default). 1 - 4 are the number of the bags that go from right to left from that big bag.  <br>  <br> This simple macro works well for bandaging after a battle. If you are looking for an in battle macro, you could add this to the end of it:  <br>  <br> /script TargetLastEnemy();  <br> /script AttackTarget();</blockquote> <br>  <br> This is by on means the end all be all of the WOW UI and all its functions, but this does give you a good idea what is possible. <br>  <br> I have tested this, and for some reason the last line does not have me go back into melee with the LastTarget. But it does provide a one button First Aid, which is all I really needed. <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Make Shift &#8226; OverSoul &#8226; Atticus &#8226; McBane &#8226; Threepio &#8226; Wyatt Herb  &#8226; Apoch &#8226; Tom Sawyer <br> Just because your paranoid doesn't not mean I'm not after you <br> Follow the Cult | <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://www.cultofxen.com">http://www.cultofxen.com</a> <br> Ner'zhul PvP - Pacific Server <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=22852&topic=79108902">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=79112763" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=195775">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=195775">Post History</a></td></tr>
